title: tiger_captain
body:
"Tiger Captain" (タイガーキャプテン) was a plastic [[science_fiction|sci-fi]] [[tank]] model released in 1968 by [[Aoshima Bunka Kyouzai]].
The front half was an [[armored_vehicle|armored car]], and the back half was a box-shaped tank with [[caterpillar tracks]] and a gun turret. The entire unit resembled a sort of [[half-track]]. It could be separated at the middle and the front half could operate independently. 
There were several variations of the toy having different sizes and costs with additional spring action or remote controlled motors and such. Almost all the models were equipped with a spring-loaded [[missile]] launch function.

This toy, along with "Thunder Captain" also released by Aoshima, was one of the most successful "original" sci-fi [[mecha]] models in Japan, and was re-released time and again with only minor changes. 
The two models, however, called attention to copyright issues at the time. Tiger Captain's front half was almost identical to the [[Spectrum Pursuit Vehicle]] from [[Captain Scarlet and the Mysterons]] and Thunder Captain's mimicked that of the [[Spectrum Patrol Car]] from the same show. 
Furthermore, the gun turrets are the spitting image of the British Chieftain tank. 

h4.See also

* Tiger Captain's photo (from "Okada Toshio's":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toshio_Okada site): http://www.netcity.or.jp/OTAKU/okada/collection/2418.html

title: hanzo_(world_heroes)
body:
[b]Hanzo Hattori Masanari[/b] (服部 半蔵, [i]Hattori Hanzō[/i]) is the protagonist of the [[World Heroes]] competitive fighting [[video game]] series. 

Hanzo is based on the [[Japan]]ese historical figure of the same name, who was head of a [[ninja]] clan in Iga and was born in August 10, 1555.

He is [[fuuma_kotarou_(world_heroes)|Fuuma Kotarou]]'s rival. In his initial planning stages, he bore a very striking resemblance to Ryu from Street Fighter. Hanzo's hairstyle and padded outfit were devised to give his design its own uniqueness. His IQ from his World Heroes profile is listed as unfathomable.

title: fuuma_kotarou_(world_heroes)
body:
[b]Kotaro Fuuma[/b] (風魔 小太郎, [i]Fūma Kotaro[/i]), often referred to by his last name, "Fuuma" (フウマ), is a character from the [[World Heroes]] competitive fighting [[video game]] series. 

Fuuma is based on the [[Japan]]ese historical figure of the same name, who was head of the Fuuma [[ninja]] clan and was born in April 2, 1555. 

He is [[hanzo_(world_heroes)|Hanzo Hattori]]'s rival. His IQ is said to be "higher than a monkey's".

title: shura_(world_heroes)
body:
[b]Shura[/b] (シュラ, ชูรา), also known as [b]Shura Nai Khanomtom[/b], is a character from the [[World Heroes]] competitive fighting [[video game]] series. 

Shura is a legendary and ancient Muay Thai champion that entered the tournament in order to fulfill his training, and to prove his strength against warriors from different times as well.   

He was born in the [[Thailand]] in June 27, 1742.

The character is based in the famous Muay Thai legend "Nai Khanom Tom":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nai_Khanom_Tom#Folklore. His mode of dress closely mirrors [[Sagat]] from the [[Street Fighter]] franchise.

title: yanagiba_kiyoshi
body:
Original character by [[Rakurakutei Ramen]] in the Karin-dou series.

He goes to the same school as [[ujikintoki_tamaryu|Tamaryu]] and the other youkai school crowd, vaguely making him part of that cast.  However, he is mostly defined by being the love interest of [[Shiraishi Sara]]. He almost never appears outside of her presence, and usually only while being glomped on by her. 

Because of this, he frequently is only referenced as "My Darling!"

Kiyoshi is a frog-youkai, which is favored prey of the sort of serpent-youkai Sara is, making her affections more than slightly uncomfortable.  

He also has the distinction of being one of the very few named male characters in the series, even if he never takes an active role in much.
